olive oil
2 clove garlic
1 stalk celery
1 carrot
1 packet fresh lasagne sheet
1 packet pork mince
1 sachet Aussie Spice Blend
1 packet passata
1 packet Red Wine Jus
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
¼ cup water
40 g butter
2 tbs plain flour
1 cup milk
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 tomato
1 packet Rocket leaves
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 packet diced bacon

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Finely chop garlic and celery. Grate carrot.
• Slice fresh lasagne sheet in half widthways.

 • In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook pork mince and diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add celery and carrot and cook until tender, 6-7 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add Kiwi spice blend and garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add passata, red wine jus, chicken-style stock powder and the water. Stir to combine and cook until slightly thickened, 1-2 minutes. Season to taste.

• Heat a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add the butter and plain flour and cook, stirring, until a thin paste forms, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from heat, then slowly whisk in the milk. Whisk until smooth.
• Stir through grated Parmesan cheese, then season with salt and pepper.

• Spoon roughly 1/4 of the pork filling into a baking dish, then top with a fresh lasagne sheet and some shredded Cheddar cheese. Repeat with remaining filling, lasagne sheets and cheese.
• Finish with a final lasagne sheet, then pour over the cheesy white sauce.
• Bake lasagne until filling is bubbling and top is golden brown, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice radish.
• In a large bowl, combine radish, rocket leaves, a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

• Divide pork, bacon and red wine lasagne between plates.
• Serve with rocket salad. Enjoy!